jnxCfgMgmt.name: jnxCfgMgmt
jnxCfgMgmt.contactinfo: Juniper Technical Assistance Center Juniper Networks, Inc. 1194 N. Mathilda Avenue Sunnyvale, CA 94089 E-mail: support@juniper.net
jnxCfgMgmt.description: This MIB module defines objects used for managing the configuration of Juniper products.

JnxCmCfChgSource.name: JnxCmCfChgSource
JnxCmCfChgSource.description: Identifies the source of config event.

JnxCmRescueCfgState.name: JnxCmRescueCfgState
JnxCmRescueCfgState.description: Identifies the state of the rescue configuration.

jnxCmCfgChgLatestIndex.name: jnxCmCfgChgLatestIndex
jnxCmCfgChgLatestIndex.description: The index in jnxCmCfgChgEventTable for the latest configuration change event.

jnxCmCfgChgLatestTime.name: jnxCmCfgChgLatestTime
jnxCmCfgChgLatestTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the configuration was last changed. If the management subsystem was reset after the last configuration change, this object will return 0.

jnxCmCfgChgLatestDate.name: jnxCmCfgChgLatestDate
jnxCmCfgChgLatestDate.description: The date and time when the configuration was last changed.

jnxCmCfgChgLatestSource.name: jnxCmCfgChgLatestSource
jnxCmCfgChgLatestSource.description: The source of the configuration event.

jnxCmCfgChgLatestUser.name: jnxCmCfgChgLatestUser
jnxCmCfgChgLatestUser.description: The name of the logged in user. The length is zero if not available or not applicable.

jnxCmCfgChgMaxEventEntries.name: jnxCmCfgChgMaxEventEntries
jnxCmCfgChgMaxEventEntries.description: The maximum number of entries that can be held in jnxCmCfgChgEventTable.

jnxCmCfgChgEventTable.name: jnxCmCfgChgEventTable
jnxCmCfgChgEventTable.description: A table of configuration events on this router.

jnxCmCfgChgEventEntry.name: jnxCmCfgChgEventEntry
jnxCmCfgChgEventEntry.description: Information about a configuration event on this router.

jnxCmCfgChgEventIndex.name: jnxCmCfgChgEventIndex
jnxCmCfgChgEventIndex.description: This object identifies a specific configuration change event. Monotonically increasing values will be assigned by the snmp subsystem to each event as it occurs. If the snmp subsystem is reset, these index values will be reset as well.

jnxCmCfgChgEventTime.name: jnxCmCfgChgEventTime
jnxCmCfgChgEventTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the event occurred.

jnxCmCfgChgEventDate.name: jnxCmCfgChgEventDate
jnxCmCfgChgEventDate.description: The system date and time when the event occurred.

jnxCmCfgChgEventSource.name: jnxCmCfgChgEventSource
jnxCmCfgChgEventSource.description: The source of the configuration event.

jnxCmCfgChgEventUser.name: jnxCmCfgChgEventUser
jnxCmCfgChgEventUser.description: The name of the logged in user. The length is zero if not available or not applicable.

jnxCmCfgChgEventLog.name: jnxCmCfgChgEventLog
jnxCmCfgChgEventLog.description: The log of the configuration event. The length is zero if not available.

jnxCmRescueChgTime.name: jnxCmRescueChgTime
jnxCmRescueChgTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the rescue configuration was last changed. If the management subsystem was reset after the last configuration change, this object will return 0.

jnxCmRescueChgDate.name: jnxCmRescueChgDate
jnxCmRescueChgDate.description: The date and time when the rescue configuration was last changed.

jnxCmRescueChgSource.name: jnxCmRescueChgSource
jnxCmRescueChgSource.description: The source of the rescue configuration event.

jnxCmRescueChgUser.name: jnxCmRescueChgUser
jnxCmRescueChgUser.description: The name of the logged in user. The length is zero if not available or not applicable.

jnxCmRescueChgState.name: jnxCmRescueChgState
jnxCmRescueChgState.description: The current state of the rescue configuration.

jnxCmCfgChange.name: jnxCmCfgChange
jnxCmCfgChange.description: Notification of a configuration management event as recorded in jnxCmCfgChgEventTable.

jnxCmRescueChange.name: jnxCmRescueChange
jnxCmRescueChange.description: Notification of the latest rescue configuration change.
